        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 28 at 5:32AM CDT until July 28 at 6:00AM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>SVRILX

The National Weather Service in Lincoln has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Fulton County in west central Illinois...
Southern Knox County in west central Illinois...

* Until 600 AM CDT.

* At 532 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Knoxville to near Galesburg to near Abingdon,
moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Severe thunderstorms will be near...
Abingdon and Knoxville around 540 AM CDT.
Maquon and St. Augustine around 545 AM CDT.

This includes Interstate 74 between mile markers 44 and 64.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
